# Files/directories the Tauri dev-mode watcher must NOT treat as "source
# changed, rebuild." These trees get touched by incidental filesystem
# activity (OS index updates, .pyc lazy writes, etc.) and each touch kicks
# off a full `cargo run` rebuild — so dev mode loops forever.
#
# These paths are still bundled into release builds via
# `tauri.conf.json → bundle.resources`; the watcher exclusion only affects
# dev-mode rebuild triggers.

# Bundled CPython runtime (~50k files, Python writes .pyc's on import).
resources/

# Cargo build output (Tauri should already skip this, but be explicit).
target/

# Tauri-generated schemas.
gen/
